Illustrations of the International Phonetic Association (IPA)

The map below shows (approximate) locations of languages for which there is an Illustration in the Journal of the International Phonetic Association. Green markers denote Illustrations that also appear in the Handbook of the International Phonetic Association.

Click on the pin on the map to identify the language and follow the link to the publication and recordings, where available. Languages marked with * have multiple pins.

Use text search to locate languages by name. Clicking on links at the end of the page will zoom to the language pin.

Please zoom in further if your selected language isn't immediately visible. Some language locations are in close proximity and overlap one another in the standard view.

Please use the github issue tracker to report problems.

Congratulations to

  • the authors of Kalasha (Bumburet variety) winners of the inaugural JIPA "Most Illustrative Illustration" prize.

  • the shortlisted illustrations - Ambel, Kejom (Babanki) and Zhushan Mandarin.



Funded by the Australian Research Council, and LaTrobe University Linguistics and Phonetics.

Last update: 07 February, 2023.
